      • diffTravelTo

        public void diffTravelTo(double x,
                         double y,
                         double theta)
        Travels to point given in arguments by referencing odometer value Correction occurs along the way using two front mounted light sensors Finishes with heading facing corresponding Y direction traversed (eg. up = 0 degrees, down = 180 degrees) Assuming: on an intersection of two grid lines
        Parameters:
        x - - in cartesian coordinates
        y - - in cartesian coordinates
        theta - - does odometry correction about end point if true, orients facing 0 degrees
